The former president missed a deadline to file an answering affidavit to an application for a contempt of court charge. Jacob Zuma has refused to attend the State Capture Commission recently, stating he wanted to appeal the decision by Justice Raymond Zondo not to recuse himself. Legal expert Nthabiseng Dubazana from Dubazana Attorney, discusses this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma has missed the deadline to file an answering affidavit to the state capture commission's application for contempt of court charge. Zuma is refusing to return to the commission unless Justice Raymond Zondo recuses himself. READ: ANC Top Six resolve to give Zuma 'space' Legal expert Nthabiseng Dubazana says Zuma should respond late, rather than not respond at all, to a bid to have him declared in contempt of court.